    <p><a href="http://people.csail.mit.edu/billf/talks/10minFreeman2013.pdf">Elements of a Successful Graduate Career</a></p>

    <blockquote>
      <p>I think the most important thing in research is a story ‚Äì not a theorem or an algorithm ‚Äì but the story that makes the theorem or algorithm interesting and exciting. ¬†¬†It‚Äôs important to have an ‚Äúear‚Äù for a good story‚Ä¶ when do the stories make sense, when are they bogus? ~ Tomas Lozano-Perez.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <blockquote>
      <p>The best students are possessed by a problem. They‚Äôre independent. They teach their advisors. They don‚Äôt do what they‚Äôre told‚Ä¶they do something more interesting. ~ Leslie Kaelbling</p>
    </blockquote>

